<headline>Winter Storm Warning issued January 06 at 10:08PM EST until January 07 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM EST
FRIDAY...
* WHAT...Heavy snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to 8
inches.
* WHERE...Ottawa, Allegan, Kalamazoo and Van Buren counties.
* WHEN...Until 10 AM EST Friday.
* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The heaviest snow tonight will likely fall
between Holland and South Haven which is where the main snow
band will come ashore. Locations like Glenn, Bangor and
Bloomingdale should see some of the heaviest snow overnight.
Inch per hour snow rates and whiteout conditions can be expected
at times.</description>
<instruction>If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.</instruction>
